a.xlink:title:
eya_def_tools.data_models.energy_assessment.EnergyAssessment
Energy assessment details and results.
Fields: gross_energy_assessment: Details and results for the assessment of gross energy yield. wind_uncertainty_assessment: Details of the wind related uncertainty assessment. plant_performance_assessment: Plant performance loss assessment categories including results. net_energy_assessment: Details and results for the assessment of net energy yield.

eya_def_tools.data_models.scenario.Scenario
Single unique energy yield assessment scenario.
Fields: id: Optional unique identifier of the scenario, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. label: Label of the scenario. description: Optional description of the scenario, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments: Optional comments on the scenario, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. is_main_scenario: Optional flag to specify whether or not it is the main scenario in the report. Default is None. wind_farm_ids: List of the IDs for all wind farms included in the scenario. Each ID refers to a wind farm configuration data object within the 'wind_farms' section of the top-level of the EYA DEF document. Only wind farms for which turbine interaction effects are modelled shall be included. turbine_wind_resource_assessment: Wind resource assessment at the turbine locations. energy_assessment: Energy assessment details and results, including gross energy, plant performance, net energy and uncertainties.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_resource.TurbineWindResourceAssessment
Wind resource assessment at the turbine locations.
Fields: wind_resource_assessment_id_reference: The ID of the wind resource assessment on which the turbine wind resource assessment is based. This must refer to an ID of a wind resource assessment included at the top level of the EYA DEF. The schema requires that a turbine wind resource assessment is based on only one wind resource assessment. description: Optional description of the turbine wind resource assessment, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments: Optional comments on the turbine wind resource assessment, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. weighting: Optional specification of the weighting applied to estimate the wind resource at the turbine location(s),relevant for example when predictions from different measurement stations were weighted individually at each turbine based on representativeness. Default is None. results: Results of the wind resource assessment at the turbine location(s).
